data.meta_description: Charlotte (1769-1818) was the daughter of Queen Charlotte’s brother, Charles, Grand Duke of Mecklenburg-Strelitz. In 1785, she married Frederick, Duke of Saxe-Hildburghausen, who inherited the additional duchy of Altenburg in 1826.The miniature’s case is engraved with Charlotte’s name but it is possible she may have been wrongly identified as the portrait here bears little resemblance to a confirmed image of the duchess by Henry Daniel Thielke, known from an engraving by Anton Karcher...
